 88  -- Interestingly, there does not seem to be a way to express this relation using a forward map.
 89  -- Given a filter `f` on `α`, we want a filter `f'` on `β` such that `r.preimage s ∈ f` if
 90  -- and only if `s ∈ f'`. But the intersection of two sets satsifying the lhs may be empty.
 91  
 92  def rcomap' (r : rel α β) (f : filter β) : filter α :=
id                    └─┘ ┴ ┴       └────┘ ┴    └────┘ ┴
src                   └─┘           └────┘      └────┘
typ                   └─┘ ┴ ┴       └────┘ ┴    └────┘ ┴
doc                   └─┘
 93  { sets             := rel.image (λ s t, r.preimage s ⊆ t) f.sets,
id                         └───────┘    ┴ ┴  ┴└───────┘ ┴ ┴ ┴  ┴└───┘
src                        └───────┘          └───────┘   ┴     └───┘
